.TH panCenter  22.14 "Fri Oct 06 02:12:27 2023" 
.SH Name \fBpanCenter\fR \-  Pans in the viewable window to the center point defined by the specified coordinates
.SH Syntax \fBpanCenter\fR   [-help]  <x y> 
.P Pans in the viewable window to the center point defined by the specified coordinates. Use this command at any stage of the design flow to view the design area around a specific point. 
.SH Parameters    "\fB-help\fR" Prints a brief description that includes type and default information for each panCenter parameter.  For a detailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use the man command: man panCenter.  "\fB<x y>\fR" Specifies the x and y coordinates of the center point. 
.SH Example
.P The following command pans the viewable window to the center point (x=100, y=200)
.P panCenter 100 200 
.SH Related Information
